#X text 51 84 [keytrack~] maps MIDI pitch input from a keyboard and outputs a function you can use to control things like a filter cutoff. The output is pitch ratio value with MIDI pitch 60 (middle C) as an unaltered reference point (ratio 1) by default. Hence \, the mapping occurs above and down the reference point or range (as you can set a lower and upper reference points forming an unaltered range). The tracking amount affects the mapping amount \, where a minimum value of 0 sets no tracking (all ratios are equal to 1)., f 67;
